node.text:
Hugo welcomes you in to his newly updated nursery! Just a few tweaks here & there to mirror his transition from babe in arms to lively tot.

Are you looking to upgrade your space for a growing little one? Hugo recommends adding a canopy reading corner & a play area, with lots of fun toy storage! 

TAP “view products” in reel view mode to shop Hugo’s room

📷 huge thanks to the lovely @graciellehome

To paper, or not to paper, that is the question. 

What’s your preference for kids’ rooms? Wallpaper, all paint, panelling, a feature wall? We love a good mix here, but we have a special spot for this dramatic Katie Scott & Ferm Living animals FSC certified wallpaper 😍 it’s styled to perfection in this sweet nursery 🙌

TAP to shop this magnificent look & head to stories to browse more wallpaper

 📷 thanks to the fabulous @arnoldandthecaterpillar

node.text:
🐯 G-I-V-E-A-W-A-Y 🐯

W I N: MamaToyz Kule Learning Tower 🐯 Perfect for the kitchen, playroom or any fun activities with hard to reach places. With a sweet neutral Tiger design, this handy tower is height adjustable & suitable from 12 months. There are so many benefits to having your little helper safely join in with tasks around the home like baking, washing up, decorating & cooking! 

Want to know how to enter?

🧡 SAVE this post
🧡 TAG a friend 
🧡 FOLLOW @scandiborn & @mamatoyz_uk 

Fancy some extra entries??

🧡 COMMENT your little one’s fave thing to help bake
🧡 SHARE to stories & tag us
🧡 LIKE this post
🧡 TAG more friends (new comment per tag)

Ends midnight (BST) Monday 13th September - WINNER to be announced via stories on 14th September. UK entrants only.

Instagram does not sponsor, endorse, or associate.

❗️Please note: We will never set up a separate account for winners/ prizes. 

📷 thank you to the wonderful @june_ira

node.text:
Easy Pizza Pinwheels

Need some packed lunch inspo? Or maybe your little ones are heading home ravenous & need a fun tasty snack? These puff pastry pinwheels & twists are also great for weaning babes!

What would you put in yours? Our favourites are chicken & halloumi! 

INGREDIENTS

🥐  ready roll puff pastry
🥫 sauce
🫑 toppings
🧀 cheese
🥚 egg or milk for wash 

HOW TO

1. Spread sauce on puff pastry
2. Add toppings like veggies, meat & herbs
3. Sprinkle cheese
4. Roll it up tight
5. Cut in to 2-3cm thick disks
6. Egg wash & pop on a non stick tray
7. Bake for 12-15 mins or until puffy & golden
8. Serve hot or cold

For the twists: cut your topped pastry in to 3-4cm wide strips & twist!

You can TAP to shop all the fabulous Liewood tableware
